# Code Organization

## App Code

- `apps/multichoice/lib/app` contains app setup, routing, theme wiring, auth/app layout, and app-level exports.
- `apps/multichoice/lib/layouts` contains layout-level widgets such as the home layout and tabs.
- `apps/multichoice/lib/presentation` contains pages, feature UI, feature widgets, dialogs, and presentation utilities.
- `apps/multichoice/lib/utils` contains app-only utilities such as product tour helpers.
- Follow the existing folder near the change before creating a new one.

## Package Code

- `packages/core/lib/src/application` contains Bloc state, events, and behavior coordination.
- `packages/core/lib/src/services`, `repositories`, `controllers`, and `wrappers` use interfaces plus implementations.
- `packages/models/lib/src` contains DTOs, database models, API models, enums, mappers, and analytics models.
- `packages/ui_kit/lib/src` contains reusable UI components and constants.
- `packages/theme/lib/src` contains theme extensions and color definitions.

## File Shape

- Keep files focused and consistent with nearby naming.
- Prefer small private widget files with `part`/`part of` only where that pattern already exists locally.
- Keep `part` declarations alphabetical.
- Use `export.dart` barrel files rather than `index.dart`.
- Add trailing commas for stable formatting.

